The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	London: Surreys plans to rope in Indian leg-spinner Piyush Chawla did not materialise after the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) refused him permission to play in county cricket. Surrey, which signed former Pakistan captain Younis Khan on a deal that will last until mid-July, said in a statement that Chawla failed to get BCCIs nod and hence would not join the side.        
	Mumbai: The Andhra Cricket Association vice-president GVK Rangaraju has been appointed as the manager of the Indian team for the upcoming tour of Zimbabwe, BCCI sources said. The team is to depart from Mumbai in the early hours of May 26, the sources said.        
	Calcutta: India captain Bhaichung Bhutia has been conferred honorary life membership of Portugal Football Players Association thus joining a list of all time greats including Cristiano Ronaldo, Luis Figo and Nuno Gomes.         
	Sao Paulo: Chelsea playmaker Deco says he wants to return to Brazilian football and has had talks with Fluminense. The Brazilian-born Portugal midfielder said on Tuesday he wishes to play in Brazil again.          
	Madrid: Real Mallorca have applied to the courts to go into voluntary administration in the next few days in a bid to sort out their finances, the Spanish club have said. Mallorca have been struggling with a debt of around $103.4 million and attempts to find a buyer to invest money into the club have so far been unsuccessful.        
	Frankfurt: Bayern Munich captain Mark van Bommel says the rift between striker Luca Toni and coach Louis van Gaal started when the Italian fell asleep at the table during a team lunch on the Dutchmans second day on the job.        
	New Delhi: Mahesh Bhupathi and Rohan Bopanna made the doubles quarter-finals of the ATP 250 event in Nice with their respective partners, according to the information reaching here. Bhupathi and Max Miryni of Belarus beat Brit Ross Hutchins and Jordan Kerr of Australia 6-1, 7-5 while Bopanna and Aisam-ul-Haq Qureshi had to toil hard to beat Simon Greul of Germany and Rogier Wassen of the Netherlands 7-5, 6-7(6), 10-4 in their first round.        
	London: American tennis player Wayne Odesnik was handed a two-year ban from competition by the International Tennis Federation (ITF) on Wednesday for a doping violation.        
	New Delhi: Indian womens team squandered a two-goal lead to settle for a 2-2 draw against New Zealand in the third hockey Test at the Kett Capital Hockey Stadium in Napier, according to information reaching here.      
